{"/service/ndnp/wa/batch_wa_canvasback_ver02/data/sn87093436/00200291463/1949060101/0203.xml":{"full_text":"THE SCANDINAVIAN AMERICAN\nSwedish Book (in Olympic Games\n1948 considered Best Available\nSweden's first 1948 gold medal winner. skater Ake Seyffarth.\nand the beautiful U. S. diving champion Vicki Draws. winncr of\ntwo gold medils in London. are among the many winners pictured\nin \u201cOlymplaboken 1948.\"\n\u201cOlympiaboken 1948\" is the name\nof a most fascinziting book which\nrecently was published in Swedish\nby Mr. Lennart Brunnhage. The\nauthor, who has been Swedish div\nSTANWOOD\nStanwood Millwork\nBOB and DICK MYGATT\nCabinets Sash Doors\nFrames Detail Millwork\nStanwood Phone \u201c1(21151\nHazel C. Hall, Broker\nReal Estate Broker\nGood Farms Good Homes\nGood Water Front\nFARM FINANCING\nBox 152 Phone \u201c1\u2018 14\nStanwood\nJ. E. HAMILTON\n8: SON, INC.\nLumber\nBuilding Materials\nMillwork Cement Brick\nTile Paint\nPhone W.(\u2018. 781\nStanwooq\nGilbertson\nHardware Company\nMAYTAG\nSales and Service\nElsi. StBnWOOd Ph. P90. 390\nOBERGBACKSTROM\nMOTORS, INC.\nSales FORD Service\nEAST STANWOOD\nBody Work Wrecker Service\nFRED MISNER, JR.\nCHEVRON SERVICE\nRPM MOTOR OIL\nAtlas Tires Batteries\nPHONE W.C. 1431\nEn: Stanwood, Wash.\nHARTNEYS\nStanwood\nMichaela-Stern Suits\nArrow Shirts\nIla-dew lists\nlllckok Bolt. uni Suspender-\nPoulleton Woolen\nnolepi-oot Hosiery\ning champion no less than nine\nteen times and is considered Eu\nrope's foremost representative in\nhis field, has published works on\nOlympic Games before, but it is\ngenerally agreed that his latest\nbook tops all others. The Swe\ndish Athletic Union purchased 65\nbooks as gifts to well known per\nsons connected with athletic un\nions all over the world. One of\nthese. the well known writer Bill\nHenry. says: \u201cCongratulations to\nLennart Brunnhage who has add\ned to the already great contribu\ntion of his nation to the success of\nthe Olympic Games.\"\nThe \"Olympiaboken\" which is\nprinted in Swedish. contains no\nless than 700 pictures from the\nwinter games in St. Moritz. and\nthe.Summer Games in London,\nand it seems that every one of\nthese photos is perfect. In addi\ntion to text and pictures. the book\nalso contains a large number of\nlists of results, not only of the la\ntest Games. but from 1896 on; al\nso complete tables on world\u2019s rec\nords in every b\u2018anch of athletic\ncompetition.\nThe book, which is of special in\nterest for Swedes and Americans.\nas these two peoples dominated\nthe 1948 Games. costs $6.50 ($9.59\nin special luxurious binding). and\nanyone interested in buying it, can\nsend check or money order for\nthis amount to Porath Magn\nheim, 95 Liberty Street, New\nYork 6, N. Y., and a copy will be\nsent by return mail. If not com\npletely satisfied, buyer may re\nturn the book and have the pur\nchase price refunded.\nBook dealers. organizations and\nprivate parties who wish to retail\nthe book will receive usual dis\ncount for larger quantities. Con\ntact above firm in New York for\nfurther details.\nNews In Brief:\nTwo new research institutes\nwere recently inaugurated at the\nCarolinian Hospital in Stockholm\nIby Crown Prince Gustaf Adolf.\nIOne is a Pharmacological Insti\nltutc and the other 8. Physiological\nInstitute.\nWalter Galonson. Assistant Pro\nfessor of Economic at Harvard\n(University. formcr Labor Attache\nEat the American Embassy in Olso,\u2018\n{has published a survey of the Nor-j\n|wegian labor movement entitle;\n\u201cLabor in Norway.\" This is the\nfirst detailed study of Norwegian\nlabor to appear in English. Pubc\n\ufb01shers\u2014Harvard University Press,\nCambridge 38. Mass. Price $5.00.\nOne hundred and ten major\nSwedish c0mmunities have \u201cadopt\ned\" towns in one or more of the\nneighboring countries under\u2018 the\nauspices of the Society Norden.\u2019\nwhich has branches in all the\nScandinavian countries. An ex\nchange of school children between\nthese places is planned for t he\nsummer.\nUN. Secretary General 'I\u2018rygve\nLie has accepted an invitation to\naddress the Danish Common Coun\ncil for the United Nstions in\nCopenhagen on August 14.\nNorway To Export\nFrozen Berries\nThe introduction of modern\nfreezing and packing methods is\nnow promising foreign tables a\nNorwegian taste treat hitherto re\nserved for more immediate mar\nkets. Wild berries. particularly\nblue berries and lingon berries.\nwhich for many years have been\nexported to England and the Con\ntinent, have long been known for\ntheir exceptionally fine flavor.\nShipping problems,_ however,\nhave hitherto limited the market\narea of this highly popular pro\nduct. and exports to more distant\nareas have generally taken the\nform of jams, jellies. and various\nother preserved products.\nModern fruit freezing. in the\nmeantime, has placed this trade\non an entirely new basis. Imme\ndiately after Norway\u2018s liberation.\nexperts were sent to the United\nStates to study the latest freezing\nmethods and to initiate market\nresearch.\nIn 1946 a modern fruit freezing\nplant was set up in the center of\nthe wild berry districts where\nfresh berries are frozen into stone\nhard pellets within a few hours af\nter picking. Carefully cleaned.\ngraded. and packed in cartons with\naluminum tops and bottoms, the\nnew product is finding a ready\nmarket abroad.\n{17,000 Tourists Visit\nSweden Jam-March\nSTOCKHOLM.\u2014\u2014More than 17.-\n000 tourists from abroad visited\nSweden in the first quarter of 1949,\naccording to official statistics.\nFinnsg Americans. Britons anc\u2018l\nDutch ranked the list in the above\norder.\n1 King Frederik and Queen Ingrid\ngexpect this summer to pay a visit\nto the Faroe Islands on board the\n{Royal yacht \u201cDannebrog.\u201d\nARLINGTON\nARLINGTON COLD\nSTORAGE\nFOOD LOCKERS\nCustom Hickory Smoked\nCuring\nFresh Cured Meats\n\u201c'holesale Retail\nPhone 342\nARLINGTON SAND\nGRAVEL\nREADY-MIX CONCRETE\nCrushed Rock for Driveways\nPhone 1381\nARLINGTON\nSTATE BANK\nComplete Banking Service\nPHONE 751 ARLINGTON\nCOR DZ\nBATTERY SHOP\nComplete\nCar and Electrical\nService\nPhone 722\nUNION MILL (10.\nWest Coast Forest Products!\nPhone I 82\nWarmer Air Melts\nSweden\u2019s Glaciers\nSTOCKHOLM.~~ Increased radi\nation of heat from the air as re\nsult of higher summer tempera\ntures and longer periods of melt\u2014\ning. in the first place, can be held\nas the factor mainly responsiblu\nfor the steady recession of Swe\nden's glaciers, acoording to studies\nmade for some years by Dr. Carl\nChristian Walle\u2018n. who on May 24\npresented a thesis on the subject\nso closely allied with climatological\nchanges observed in many regions\nduring the past decades.\nThe same phenomena has been ob\nserved by Scandinavian scientists\nin Greenland and Spitzbm'gvn al\nthough lengthy and systematic re\nsearch in these areas (war a num\nber of years has not been possible.\nSweden Awards\nPioneer Medals\nPioneer Medals have been?\nawarded by the Swedish gm'ernn\nment to four residents of Seattlef\nWinners were given the decora\ntions for their outstanding work\nin the service of Swedish people\nin the United States.\nWinners were Miss Herina I. Ek\nlind, superintendent of Swedish\nHospital: Gus Backman, Seattle\nimpresario: Einar Carlson. pub\nlisher of Seattle\u2018s Swedish lan\nguage newspaper, Svenska Posten,\nand A. N. Rumin, retired official of\nthe Swedish American Line.\nPresentations were made Sat\nurday. May 14. by Erik Bohvv\nman. Swedish ambassador to the\nUnited States. at a dinner in the\nOlympic Hotel. More than 350\npersons attended.\nNorwegian Forest\nExperts 0n Study\nTour Of Northwest\nOn the last lap of a three\nmonths\u2019 ECA tour of American\ntimber operations. two Norwe\ngian forestry experts arrived in\nPortland to begin a study of ro-\nforestation procedures in the Pa\u2014\ncific Northwest.\nThey are Professor Elias Mork\nof the forestry experimental sta\ntion at Aas. Norway, and Pro\nfessor Franz Germeten of the\nSteinkjor. Norway. forester school.\nThey are accompanied by Mrs\u2018\nGermeten, who is traveling at her\nown expense and acting as inter\nproter.\nArlington\nTheir primary mission. they ex\nplained. is to investigate seed\nsources in their natural habitat in\nthe Pacific Northwest with the\nhope west coast species may be\nused more extensively in reforest\nation in Norway.\nDouglas fir. which has proven\none of the fastest-growing re\nforesting species in Europe. and\nhemlock will be the two chief spe\ncies studied in Oregon and Wash\nington.\nA rlingwn\nTheir studies may result in later\npurchases of seed here for Nonve\ngian reforesting activities. they\nadded.\nDr. Clarence Crafoord\nHonored By France\nSTOCKHOLM. Dr. Clarence\nCrafoord. Swedish surgeon. whose\ncardiac operatlons have attracted\ninternational attention. has been\nmade an honorary doctor of medi\u00bb\ncine by the University of Gre-'\nnoble. in France. On his fiftieth\nbirthday. May 28. Dr. Crumrd\nreceived the proceeds of a ns-I\ntion-wide collection of funds in;\nSweden by which his rose-rem\nwork dad that 0! his associates in.\nthe field of hurt surgery will be\u2018\nfimmciuly (unnamed. People in\nall walks of life have contributed?\nHis two most ncent pstients are:\na nine-yen old boy from South=\nAfrica and a seventeen-year old:\ngirl from Czechoslovakia. i\nArlington 1\nArlington\nSweden Swept By\nA Violent Storm\nI STOCKHOLM. A devastating\nidust storm blanketed southern\nimost Sweden recently, cow-ring\nparts of the provinces of Sk\u00e9ne.\n.\u201cSweden\u2019s granary,\" Blekinge, lo\nlcated to the east. and Halland, on\n\u2018the south-west coast. The wind\n3velocity reached hurricane speed.\nand the fertile Kristianstad plain.\n:was hidden by gigantic dust\nclouds. Drifts of sand towered\nalong the highways which became\niimpassable, even to automobil~~s.\njSometimes objects only a few feet.\n\u2018away were hidden from view, and\nlevei'ywhere work in the fields\n'Cami- to a standstill. Tons of top\n\u2018soil were swept into the sea.\nGunnar Pettersson. Sweden's\nforemost expert on SULh natural\nfphenomona and a director of the\n\u2018Government expurimental agricul-\nEtuz'al station at Ugerup, in Skane.\n;has estimated the losses in crops\nland land to tens of millions of\nlkronor.\nit A Danish delegation led by Min\nvlister of Commerce J. 0. Krag has\n.ileft for Italy to negotiate a new\n-;Italo-Danish trade agreement.\nPENDLETON\nEASTERN OREGON\nMOTOR CO.\nFORD\nSales Service\nCompietg Agltomotive\nService\nFactory Enginm-red Parts\nExpvrt Mechank\u2018s\n4\u201823 S. E. (\u2018nurt St. Phone 5\u201836\n((\u2018urnvr B\u2018h) (Nights. 1146)\nPENDLETON. ORE.\nTowing s- \\\\'rt-(-k9r Svrviw\n_\u2014 Any\u201c hon- v\nOlsen Motors, Inc.\nDODGE I\u2019LYMOI'TH\nSales and Service\nCars and Trucks\nDodge \"Juh Ruled\" Trucks\n(\u2018OMPLETE\nAl'TOMOTlYl-I SERVH \u2018E\n\u201cThe Job's Like New \\Vhen\nWe (19! Through\"\nFactory Engine-erred and lnspt\u2018ctod\nParts and Supplies\n103 K\u2019 105 S. \u201cI (\u2018ourt Ann\nl\u2019hnm- Pt-ndlvton 963\nPENDLETON. OREGON\nNIELSEN MOTEL\nSingle or Dnuhle Modern (\u2018ahins\nA\u2018 Sleeping Booms\nsteam Heat Showen\n(ins Cooking Facilities\nH. L. Nielsen. Prop.\nl Block East and 12 Block Norih\nof C nurthmmu\n115 S. E. 6m Phone 514\nPc'ndloton. ()re.\nPantonum\nCleaners 5' Dye Works\nSh-l\u2018rvswd Lustre Cleaning\nExpen (\u2018nra- For All \\\u2018our (\u2018Imlnng\n(\u2018urtalns Draperies Carpets\nl'pholsunng\nRecognized Fur (\u2018Inning\nStorage SOKVK\u2018Q\n310 S.W.Dormn Phone 81\nPendlelon. Vegan\nDOMESTIC\nLaundry fr Dry Cleaning\nCo.\nl\u2018ar\ufb02cuhr Gunmen! (19min:\nFor Ev'ery Member of \ufb02u-\nFunny\nMoth Proofing Wanner Proo\ufb01ng\nWaring App-rot Draperies\n(\u2018urtuns Rugu\ni'pholstvn-d Furniture\nPlt\u2018k-l\u2018p 8nd D\ufb02lven Service\n308 S.E.(\u2018ourt I\u2019h. 60 or 100\nPendlelon. Dru-gn-\n7","height":"21672","width":"15044"}}
